@page "/changelog"
<PageTitle>Changelog - Saascade Docs</PageTitle>

<h1 id="changelog">Changelog</h1>

<div class="doc-layout">

<main class="documentation">

    <TechCard>
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="unreleased">Unreleased</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">
                Changes that are in development and not yet released.
            </p>

            <hr />

            <h3>Added</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Documentation website with full sidebar navigation.</li>
                <li>Dark / Light theme toggle.</li>
                <li>Responsive sidebar with mobile overlay.</li>
                <li>Framework filter for Bootstrap 5, DaisyUI, and Basecoat.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Components</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Card, CardBody, CardTitle, CardsGrid</li>
                <li>Button and semantic button aliases (Accept, Cancel, Close, Delete, Destructive)</li>
                <li>Drawer, DrawerSide, DrawerContent</li>
                <li>Hero, Carousel, Figure, Navbar</li>
                <li>H1–H6, P, A, Ul, Li, Img, Div, Section, Main, Header, Footer, Column</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Design Systems</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Bootstrap 5 (Vanilla)</li>
                <li>Tailwind / DaisyUI</li>
                <li>Tailwind / Basecoat</li>
                <li>Custom: Basic1, Handdrawn (Accessible, B&amp;W, Color), Empty</li>
            </ul>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="bootstrap">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="changelog-bootstrap">Bootstrap 5 Changelog</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">Bootstrap 5 Changelog</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                The VanillaBootstrap5 design system was added with full support for the Card,
                Button, Navbar, Hero, Carousel, Figure, Drawer, and all typography and layout
                components. Semantic button aliases map to Bootstrap's color variant classes.
                The design system returns Bootstrap's CDN stylesheet and bundle script references
                automatically via DesignSystemStylesheetReferences and DesignSystemJavaScriptReferences.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="daisyui">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="changelog-daisyui">DaisyUI Changelog</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">DaisyUI Changelog</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                The DaisyUI design system was added with full support for all Saascade components.
                Card resolves to DaisyUI's card class with bg-base-100 and shadow-sm specializations.
                Button resolves to btn. The design system is CSS-only and returns the DaisyUI CDN
                stylesheet. Theme switching via the data-theme attribute on the html element is
                supported and works without any Saascade-specific configuration.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

    <TechCard Tech="basecoat">
        <section class="card">

            <h2 id="changelog-basecoat">Basecoat Changelog</h2>

            <p class="subtitle">Basecoat Changelog</p>

            <hr />

            <p>
                The Basecoat design system was added with full support for all Saascade components.
                Each component resolves to a curated set of Tailwind utility classes from the
                Basecoat library. The design system is CSS-only and returns the Basecoat CDN
                stylesheet. The implementation is independent from the DaisyUI design system and
                provides a different visual aesthetic while sharing the same Tailwind foundation.
            </p>

        </section>
    </TechCard>

</main>

<TableOfContents Items="@([
    new TocItem("changelog", "Changelog"),
    new TocItem("unreleased", "Unreleased", 2),
    new TocItem("changelog-bootstrap", "Bootstrap 5", 2),
    new TocItem("changelog-daisyui", "DaisyUI", 2),
    new TocItem("changelog-basecoat", "Basecoat", 2)
])" />

</div>
